By reason that contempt the defendant is ordered to serve 7 days in jail consecutive to any other sentence, conditional jail or prejudgment detention.  The defendant may purge contempt by doing the following:  Paying the unpaid court obligations in the amount of $337.00.  If the contempt finding is for unpaid court ordered obligations, serving the jail does not relieve the defendant of those obligations.....

Defendant Coby Dean Mckinley in court with attorney Patrick William Waters.  Defendant Coby Dean Mckinley in custody.  Jon D. Seifert appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Counsel informs court of plea agreement, defendant will plea to charge and reopen & dismiss 15TR257 cracked/damaged windshield; joint recommendation of 40 hours community service and costs; expunge possession conviction upon successful completion and no new crimes.  Court informs counsel like to impose jail and stay it and 1 year before consider expungement to demonstrate good behavior with defendant writing the court and requesting it.  Subject to plea negotiations, court reopens and dismiss 15TR257.  Advises defendant of elements/max penalties in 15CM29.  Defendant pleads no contest.  PLQ/WRF filed and reviewed. Court finds defendant's WCR & plea done knowingly & voluntarily, accepts plea and finds defendant guilty.  Atty Waters requests 6 months before requesting expungement.  Court sentences defendant to 10 days in the Pepin County Jail and stay it upon completion of 40 hours community service; pay costs $443.00 at rate of $100/mo. com. 10/1/15; approve expungement after 1 year with no new violations of law and defendant to write court a letter requesting it.
